label: maximumValueMeasure
comment: A measure of a maximum value for this sustainability characteristic.
The measure of the highest value of a range for this specified temperature, such as a maximum temperature value of fourteen degrees Celsius.
The measure of the highest value of this transport setting temperature, such as a maximum temperature value of fourteen degrees Celsius.
The measure of the maximum value for this process characteristic.
The measure of the maximum value for this specified range.
The measure of the maximum value of this instructed temperature.

domainIncludes.comment: Temperature settings instructed for storage or movement of goods.
A prominent attribute or aspect of a process.
A row, line or series, commonly used to express the difference between lowest and highest values.
A specified temperature value or range of values.
A prominent attribute or aspect of an object, such as recyclability of a product, which can meet customer needs without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.
Temperature settings for a transport movement, such as a required storage temperature range.
